{
    "cells": [
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "# **Portfolio:** Mario Casanova — Data Science & Analytics Portfolio\n",
                "## **Case Study:** A/B Testing, Optimization & Statistical Inference\n",
                "\n",
                "---\n",
                "*Note: This notebook simulates the empirical conclusion of an A/B experiment (Hypothesis Testing) on our Hardware Onboarding process. We want to determine, with mathematical rigor, if a specific mobile app initial flow variant has a causal, statistically significant impact on the Conversion Rate to paid subscriptions (Hardware-to-Subscription Attach Rate).*"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "import numpy as np\n",
                "import pandas as pd\n",
                "import scipy.stats as stats\n",
                "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
                "import seaborn as sns\n",
                "from statsmodels.stats.proportion import proportions_ztest, proportion_confint\n",
                "\n",
                "import warnings\n",
                "warnings.filterwarnings('ignore')\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.style.use('dark_background')\n",
                "sns.set_palette(\"Blues\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "### 1. Experiment Data Ingestion (Random Assignment)\n",
                "We evaluate the random partition between the Control Flow (Classic Onboarding) and the Variant (Redesigned Onboarding Flow)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "df_users = pd.read_csv('../data/hardware_users.csv')\n",
                "df_subs = pd.read_csv('../data/subscriptions.csv')\n",
                "\n",
                "df_subs['Has_Subscribed'] = 1\n",
                "df_ab = pd.merge(df_users, df_subs[['UserID', 'Has_Subscribed']], on='UserID', how='left')\n",
                "df_ab['Has_Subscribed'] = df_ab['Has_Subscribed'].fillna(0).astype(int)\n",
                "\n",
                "print(\"[*] A/B Experiment Sample Summary:\\n\")\n",
                "print(df_ab['OnboardingVersion'].value_counts())\n",
                "df_ab.head()"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "### 2. Empirical Results (Sample Conversion Rates)\n",
                "We group the binary results to observe the superficial absolute difference before applying the sensitivity thresholds of the Central Limit Theorem."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "ab_summary = df_ab.groupby('OnboardingVersion').agg(\n",
                "    Exposures=('UserID', 'count'),\n",
                "    Conversions=('Has_Subscribed', 'sum'),\n",
                "    Conversion_Rate=('Has_Subscribed', 'mean')\n",
                ")\n",
                "\n",
                "ab_summary['Conversion_Rate_Pct'] = ab_summary['Conversion_Rate'] * 100\n",
                "ab_summary"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "### 3. Hypothesis Testing: Two-Proportions Z-Test\n",
                "We establish:\n",
                "- Null Hypothesis $H_0$: $p_{variant} = p_{control}$ (The new onboarding doesn't change anything).\n",
                "- Alternative Hypothesis $H_1$: $p_{variant} > p_{control}$ (The new onboarding improves conversion).\n",
                "- Significance Level (Alpha $\alpha$): $0.05$ (95% Confidence)."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "control_results = df_ab[df_ab['OnboardingVersion'] == 'Control']['Has_Subscribed']\n",
                "variant_results = df_ab[df_ab['OnboardingVersion'] == 'Variant']['Has_Subscribed']\n",
                "\n",
                "n_con = control_results.count()\n",
                "n_var = variant_results.count()\n",
                "successes = [control_results.sum(), variant_results.sum()]\n",
                "nobs = [n_con, n_var]\n",
                "\n",
                "z_stat, pval = proportions_ztest(successes, nobs=nobs)\n",
                "(lower_con, lower_var), (upper_con, upper_var) = proportion_confint(successes, nobs=nobs, alpha=0.05)\n",
                "\n",
                "print(f\"[*] Z-Statistic (Test Statistic): {z_stat:.4f}\")\n",
                "print(f\"[*] P-Value: {pval:.4e}\")\n",
                "print(\"-------------------------------------------\")\n",
                "print(f\"[-] Control 95% Confidence Interval: [{lower_con:.4f}, {upper_con:.4f}]\")\n",
                "print(f\"[+] Variant 95% Confidence Interval: [{lower_var:.4f}, {upper_var:.4f}]\")"
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "markdown",
            "metadata": {},
            "source": [
                "### 4. Interpretation and Uncertainty Range Visualization\n",
                "The frequentist statistics decision rule dictates that if $p < \alpha$, we strongly reject $H_0$."
            ]
        },
        {
            "cell_type": "code",
            "execution_count": null,
            "metadata": {},
            "outputs": [],
            "source": [
                "fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(8, 5))\n",
                "\n",
                "rates = [control_results.mean(), variant_results.mean()]\n",
                "errors = [ (upper_con-lower_con)/2, (upper_var-lower_var)/2 ]\n",
                "\n",
                "bars = ax.bar(['Control Group', 'Variant Group'], rates, yerr=errors, capsize=10, color=['#78909c', '#29b6f6'], alpha=0.8)\n",
                "ax.set_title(\"A/B Conversion Effectiveness (95% Confidence Intervals)\", fontsize=14, pad=15)\n",
                "ax.set_ylabel(\"Average Conversion Rate\")\n",
                "\n",
                "# Add labels\n",
                "for index, bar in enumerate(bars):\n",
                "    ax.text(bar.get_x() + bar.get_width() / 2, bar.get_height() / 2,\n",
                "            f\"{rates[index]*100:.2f}%\", ha='center', color='white', fontweight='bold', fontsize=14)\n",
                "\n",
                "if pval < 0.05:\n",
                "    plt.suptitle(\"\\nBusiness Result: We Reject the Null Hypothesis (Significant Improvement)\", color='lime')\n",
                "else:\n",
                "    plt.suptitle(\"\\nBusiness Result: We Failed to Reject H0 (Inconclusive)\", color='yellow')\n",
                "\n",
                "plt.show()"
            ]
        }
    ],
